snippet.title: Moments in Time Trailer
snippet.description:
Moments in Time is a very special project funded by the Heritage Lottery Fund - an archive of creative work and memories gathered from care experienced young people in Derbyshire during the COVID-19 pandemic.
The archive contains a collection of over 400 stories, poems, photographs, artwork, films, songs and music. It also contains recordings of Derbyshire people's memories of the 1969 Moon Landings which is where our project began.
You can watch a 13 minute film in celebration of the archive here: https://youtu.be/F0ff8xrokJQ and explore the archive by appointment at the Derbyshire Record Office in Matlock.
Moments in Time is a National Lottery Heritage Fund project with support from Youth Music, Foundation Derbyshire and Derbyshire County Council's Action Grants. With partners Derbyshire Virtual School, the Amber Factory, Baby People and the Derbyshire Record Office.
